; b3_nonsnf.smt2  (SCALED — 10 tasks)
; Theory: QF_LIA  (NON-SNF baseline -- mechanical QE, big-OR/pairwise)
; Property: shared_resource = 10
; Expected: UNSAT
;
; Third encoding point. The naive AUFLIA b3_naive.smt2 encodes lock
; acquisition order via an injective+surjective AcquireSlot bijection
; (forall/exists nesting over 10! permutations). Here we mechanically
; eliminate those quantifiers via ground unrolling into an explicit
; assignment-matrix Boolean encoding (acquire[t][slot] = 0/1) with
; big-OR (each task gets some slot) + pairwise exclusion (no two tasks
; share a slot) clauses -- the SAME mechanical strategy used for PHP.
; NO structural insight ("lock enforces total order, so sum is
; invariant") is used -- that is the SNF shortcut we are isolating.
;
; Clause count: 10 big-OR + (10 choose 2)*10 = 10 + 450 = 460 clauses
; vs SNF structured: 12 simple equality assertions

